sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant GW as KServe Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant API as vLLM API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Worker as HPUWorker<br/>(in-process)
    participant Gaudi as Intel Gaudi Device<br/>SynapseAI HAL
    participant S3 as S3/MinIO Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant HF as Hugging Face Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client, Gaudi: Flow 1: Model Inference Request

    Client->>GW: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (JWT)
    GW->>RBAC: Forward (HTTPS/8443)<br/>TLS, ServiceAccount Token
    RBAC->>API: Forward (HTTP/8000)<br/>localhost, no auth
    API->>Worker: In-process call<br/>Schedule inference
    Worker->>Gaudi: Execute model forward<br/>SynapseAI graph compilation
    Gaudi-->>Worker: Inference result<br/>Token logits
    Worker-->>API: Generated tokens
    API-->>RBAC: JSON response
    RBAC-->>GW: HTTPS response
    GW-->>Client: Completion response

    Note over Worker, Gaudi: Flow 2: Multi-Card Tensor Parallelism

    participant W0 as HPUWorker Rank 0
    participant WN as HPUWorker Rank N

    W0->>WN: HCCL all-reduce<br/>Dynamic port, plaintext
    WN->>W0: Collective result<br/>HCCL protocol

    Note over Worker, S3: Flow 3: Model Loading (Startup)

    Worker->>S3: GET model weights<br/>HTTPS/443, AWS IAM / Access Key
    S3-->>Worker: Model artifacts
    Worker->>HF: GET tokenizer/config<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer Token (optional)
    HF-->>Worker: Model config files

    Note over Worker, Gaudi: Flow 4: KV Cache Disaggregation (NIXL)

    participant Prefill as Prefill Instance
    participant Decode as Decode Instance
    participant SideCh as NIXL Side Channel<br/>HTTP, plaintext

    Prefill->>SideCh: KV cache metadata<br/>Side channel port + dp_rank
    SideCh->>Decode: Transfer coordination
    Prefill->>Decode: KV cache data<br/>NIXL / RDMA, direct memory
